sequenceDiagram
    participant C as AOL 2.6 Client
    participant P as AOL4Free Patch<br/>(P3 CODE @ 0x589A)
    participant S as AOL Server
    participant B as Billing System

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        note over C,B: NORMAL CLIENT — user clicks "Chat Rooms"
        note over C: Button dispatch: Ask_DB (MOP 1)<br/>('K1', plus_pay) subparms<br/>Packed token+s_code: $96 $C5
        C->>S: K1 token + library record
        S->>B: plus_pay → billing RUNNING
        S->>C: fD packet (Chat Rooms window)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 240)
        note over C,B: PATCHED CLIENT — same action
        C->>P: K1 (Chat Rooms) outgoing
        P->>S: K1 (Chat Rooms) — forwarded unchanged
        S->>B: plus_pay → billing RUNNING
        note over P: Token table (0x589A): no special match<br/>→ default handler, '3' flag set at $0006
        note over P: Events handler fires next cycle:<br/>reads '3', clears it, sends K1 dispatch
        P->>S: K1 "Request library record"<br/>(free area address)
        S->>B: Free area → billing PAUSED
        S->>C: fD (Chat Rooms data)
        S->>P: fD (Free Area window data)
        P--xC: SUPPRESSED — $1501FB06 marker
        S->>P: fdo$Switch HideDisplay 00<br/>(Window Switch 22)
        P--xC: IGNORED — 'i' flag set at $0005
        note over C: Chat Rooms visible + billing paused
    end
